Original title: Cheyenne Autumn
Year: 1964
Duration: 160 min.
Country: United States
Director: John Ford
Screenwriter: James R. Webb
Music: Alex North
Photo: William H. Clothier
Cast: Richard Widmark, Carroll Baker, James Stewart, Karl Malden, Sal Mineo, Edward G. Robinson, Ricardo Montalban, Arthur Kennedy, Gilbert Roland
Studio: Warner Bros. Pictures
Genre: Western

Synopsis:
---------
In 1868, three hundred Cheyenne Indians forced off their land lived miserably in a barren reservation in Oklahoma .After waiting in vain for a solution of the Washington authorities, their leaders decided to undertake a long journey to their native prairies. But the escape was discovered and cavalry gavethe first combat commander Braden and eight of his men were killed. When the news broke, thousands of soldiers were sent to fight against the Cheyenne brave.
